## BFF Internal Secret (H9)

Token-issuing backend routes (`POST /auth/login`, `POST /auth/refresh`) require a
server-only shared secret so direct calls to the public Railway URL cannot obtain
JWTs without knowing `BFF_INTERNAL_SECRET`.

```typescript
import { getBffSecretHeaders } from "@/app/api/lib/getBffSecretHeaders";

await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/login`, {
  headers: {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    ...getBffSecretHeaders(),
  },
  // ...
});
```

Set the same `BFF_INTERNAL_SECRET` on Vercel and Railway (`openssl rand -base64 32`).
Optional in local dev when the backend also omits the secret.

