## Refresh Token Rotation (H7 + L8)

On every `/auth/refresh` call the backend:

1. Validates the incoming `refresh_token` cookie (forwarded by the BFF).
2. Revokes that token from the DB.
3. Returns a new access token **and** a new refresh token in JSON.

The **BFF sets both httpOnly cookies** — the backend does not use `Set-Cookie`
(the browser never talks to Nest directly for auth).

```typescript
// src/app/api/lib/backend.ts  (simplified)
import {
  getAccessTokenCookieOptions,
  getRefreshTokenCookieOptions,
} from "@/app/api/lib/authCookieOptions";

async function refreshAccessToken(cookieStore: ReadonlyRequestCookies) {
  const refreshToken = cookieStore.get("refresh_token")?.value;
  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/refresh`, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: {
      Cookie: `refresh_token=${refreshToken}`,
      ...getBffSecretHeaders(),
    },
  });

  const data = await res.json();
  if (!data.accessToken || !data.refreshToken) return null;

  cookieStore.set(
    "access_token",
    data.accessToken,
    getAccessTokenCookieOptions(),
  );
  cookieStore.set(
    "refresh_token",
    data.refreshToken,
    getRefreshTokenCookieOptions(),
  );
}
```

Shared cookie options live in `src/app/api/lib/authCookieOptions.ts`
(`httpOnly`, `secure` in production, `sameSite: 'strict'`).

