## Backend Route Protection — Global Guard + @Public()

`JwtAuthGuard` is a **global `APP_GUARD`** (registered in `AppModule`). All
endpoints are authenticated by default. Use `@Public()` to opt out:

```typescript
// src/controllers/auth.controller.ts
import { Public } from '@/common/decorators/public.decorator';

@Public()    // ✅ login is public
@Post('login')
login(@Body() dto: LoginDto) { ... }

@Public()    // ✅ refresh is public (token is validated internally)
@Post('refresh')
refresh(@Req() req: Request) { ... }
```

### ❌ WRONG: Per-controller guard with public exceptions via middleware

```typescript
// NEVER protect routes only through Next.js proxy/middleware
// The backend must always enforce JWT independently.
```

