## Environment Variables

### Backend (.env / .env.local)

```bash
JWT_SECRET=min-32-chars-cryptographically-secure  # required — app won't start without it
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=different-min-32-chars-secure  # required — app won't start without it
```

Generate with:

```bash
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
```

### Frontend (.env.local)

```bash
# Private server-side URL — do NOT prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_
API_URL=http://localhost:3002

# Must match the backend JWT_SECRET exactly.
# proxy.ts uses it to verify access token signatures on the Edge Runtime
# (server-side only — no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix means it is never sent to the browser).
JWT_SECRET=<same-value-as-backend>

# JWT_REFRESH_SECRET is NOT needed here — refresh tokens are only validated by the backend.
```

### ❌ NEVER

- Commit secrets to git
- Use short/weak secrets
- Reuse secrets across environments
- Use `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` in Server Actions or API route handlers

