## Security Checklist

Before implementing auth features:

- [ ] Using `getBackendUrl()` in all Server Actions / API route handlers?
- [ ] NOT using `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` in any server-side code?
- [ ] Proxy allowlist updated for new path segments?
- [ ] `auth/*` never in the proxy allowlist?
- [ ] Backend endpoint is either behind global `JwtAuthGuard` or decorated `@Public()`?
- [ ] Storing tokens in HTTP-only cookies (not localStorage)?
- [ ] Both `access_token` AND `refresh_token` cookies set on login and refresh?
- [ ] Refresh rotation tested (old token revoked)?
- [ ] Using `proxy.ts` (not `middleware.ts`) for frontend route gating?

